channel.title: PI weird errors, HELP! Using Java Eclipse to help!
channel.description:
I was normally using the server and I was getting an error that I didn't know how to fix, so I set it up on Eclipse, and I get these errors when I try to run server, [b]Exception in thread "main" java.lang.Error: Unresolved compilation problems: playerHandler cannot be resolved to a type Syntax error, insert "}" to complete Block Player cannot be resolved to a type PlayerHandler cannot be resolved to a variable PlayerSave cannot be resolved Client cannot be resolved to a type Syntax error, insert "else Statement" to complete IfStatement Syntax error, insert "}" to complete Block Syntax error, insert "}" to complete Block Syntax error, insert "Finally" to complete TryStatement
at server.Server.main(Server.java:171)[/b] They are all very simple and easy to find, but the coding looks completely fine to me, I know you'll want images, but it would take too many, so please add me on Skype and we can figure this out. [b]iamjmperry[/b]
Here's a pic of some of the errors, it's mostly these that are the problem. [b] Player cannot be resolved to a type PlayerHandler cannot be resolved to a variable PlayerSave cannot be resolved Client cannot be resolved to a type[/b] [img]http://i.imgur.com/FMZir.jpg[/img]

See that “catch” inside the “try” block? It needs to be outside, like

try {

}
catch (Exception e) {

}
